sentences.sentence:
The ACCC's case as initially formulated was:- (i) the form represented both that it was sent under the imprimatur of an Australian government agency and the information it sought had already been published on a register maintained by an agency affiliated with the Australian Government;
(ii) it contained deliberate mistakes intended to prompt businesses to respond; and
(iii) it failed to inform recipients that in signing and returning the form the businesses were liable to pay an amount between $1200 and $1600 annually with a minimum subscription of three years.
